<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Goemoe on 01-11-2000 01:53 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Perhaps you should look for something which tells everybody what to expect. So if you use some name with words like [i]realms, world, lands, empire[/i] in it you could build an image in the mind of the reader. If you also use some typical fantasy worlds (like wizardry, might and magic or even elder scrolls) you perhaps get the attention of someone who didn't intend to look for project C but likes this kind of game.

Though I have to admit Might and Magic is a rather stupid name, but you get the hack what it might contain...

I think we can't be of much help, since we don't know the story and it should be somewhat related to it.

But if you start a poll on it, perhaps you will ask for [b]which name would most definately get your attention[/b] instead of [i]which name do you like most...[/i]

just a thought

Goemoe

